The paper proposes a novel graph neural network architecture for spatial-temporal graph modeling, which involves learning the hidden spatial dependency in the data and handling long sequences. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories as they are the most general and encompass a wide range of topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The other categories are also relevant as they involve network analysis, neural computing, and computer vision, which are all relevant to the proposed method.
